Question. When you rub your finger along the rim of a glass, it resonates, why is 
this? Also, why does the pitch of this sound get lower when you add water to the 
glass? Asked by: Sly Fox. Answer. As your finger travels around the glass it sticks 
and slides at different points. Each stop and start causes the glass to vibrate.
